are going to magically appear

12:35.522 --> 12:38.056
and disappear,
changing their positions

12:38.091 --> 12:39.858
around this square.

12:39.893 --> 12:43.228
Travelling from their corners
to all come together.

12:43.263 --> 12:45.564
Gathering here in this corner,

12:45.599 --> 12:49.267
and landing underneath
this square.

12:49.303 --> 12:51.603
And if I can create
the illusion

12:51.638 --> 12:54.072
that those coins move
without me using my hands,

12:54.107 --> 12:55.907
well, then..

12:55.943 --> 12:57.909
I might just fool you.

12:57.945 --> 12:59.744
[audience amazement]

12:59.780 --> 13:03.081
[applause]

13:03.116 --> 13:06.051
This is magic in its purest
and simplest form.

13:06.086 --> 13:09.654
Four coins in a square,
a card over each coin.

13:09.690 --> 13:13.491
Watch closely, because
this does happen very fast.

13:13.527 --> 13:15.260
[speaking Japanese]

13:15.295 --> 13:18.129
