[applause]

13:18.165 --> 13:19.764
Was that too fast for you?
Not a problem.

13:19.800 --> 13:23.234
Everybody,
do not blink your eyes,

13:23.270 --> 13:25.637
and, uh, I'll just do it
one more time.

13:25.672 --> 13:27.072
[audience amazement]

13:27.107 --> 13:31.276
[applause]

13:31.311 --> 13:34.045
One by one, so you can
actually see the coins

13:34.081 --> 13:36.648
travelling one at a time.

13:36.683 --> 13:40.118
I'll start here openly
so you can see everything.

13:40.153 --> 13:42.854
Everybody, watch this coin...

13:42.889 --> 13:44.889
Travel.

13:44.925 --> 13:47.158
[applause]
Watch the next one...

13:47.194 --> 13:50.528
Go from the side.

13:50.564 --> 13:53.665
And the people from this side
may actually see the last one

13:53.700 --> 13:55.333
disappear from my fingertips.

13:55.369 --> 14:01.239
Watch this last coin vanish,
creating a tremor in the force

14:01.274 --> 14:03.341
as 100,000 children
watching this

14:03.377 --> 14:06.244
suddenly decide
that magic is cool.

14:06.279 --> 14:09.514
[cheering and applause]

14:12.919 --> 14:15.153
The viewers at home
may Google me now.

14:15.188 --> 14:18.089
[laughter]

14:18.125 --> 14:20.625
This time visibly,
so you actually see

14:20.661 --> 14:22.427
each coin jump.

14:22.462 --> 14:24.295
This is the part
that hits people hard.

14:24.331 --> 14:29.200
